cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a modification to CapsNets, which is a type of neural network commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on improving efficiency and reducing the number of parameters, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of tensors and matrix operations is also relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper explores the adversarial robustness of the proposed method, which is related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
